esearchers%20said%20in%20their%20study%2C%20published%20in%20the%20peer-reviewed%20journal%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcell.com%2Fcurrent-biology%2Ffulltext%2FS0960-9822(23)01304-0%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECurrent%20Biology%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EHow%2C%20you%20might%20ask%2C%20did%20scientists%20get%20here%3F%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EBats%20with%20shockingly%20giant%20penises%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWell%2C%20when%20the%20scientists%20put%20the%20bats%20under%20anesthesia%20to%20learn%20more%20about%20their%20reproductive%20biology%2C%20they%20noticed%20that%20the%20males%20were%20incredibly%20well-endowed%2C%20Nicolas%20Fasel%2C%20lead%20author%20of%20the%20paper%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Lausanne%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFasel%20explained%20that%20the%20sheer%20size%20and%20shape%20of%20the%20organ%20were%20shocking%20to%20them.%20%26quot%3BWhen%20we%20just%20had%20to%20anesthetize%20the%20bats%2C%20we%20could%20see%20their%20erection.%20And%20then%20we%20were%20just%20like%2C%20'Wow.%20What%20is%20that%3F'%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20erect%2C%20the%20bats'%20penises%20were%20on%20average%200.65%20inches%20long.%20That%20might%20sound%20small%2C%20but%20for%20an%20animal%20that's%20only%202.44%20to%203.15%20inches%20long%2C%20it's%20actually%2022%25%20of%20their%20body%20length%2C%20the%20researchers%20reported%20in%20the%20study.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E(It%20would%20be%20the%20equivalent%20of%20a%20six-foot-tall%20human%20male%20having%20a%20penis%20that%2C%20when%20erect%2C%20grew%20to%20be%20slightly%20over%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.insider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fsex-relationships%2Faverage-penis-size%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E15%20inches%20long%3C%2Fa%3E.)%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20fact%2C%20the%20researchers%20explained%20in%20the%20paper%2C%20the%20male%20bat's%20penis%20is%20seven%20times%20longer%20and%20wider%20than%20the%20female%20bat's%20vagina.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESo%20how%20does%20a%20species%20reproduce%20when%20they%20have%20a%20square%20peg%20and%20round%20hole%20situation%3F%20That's%20what%20the%20scientists%20simply%20had%20to%20find%20out%2C%20Fasel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3EA%20scientific%20peep%20show%20and%20future%20bat%20porn%20box%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%221920%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22A%20full%20body%20photograph%20of%20serotine%20bat%20lying%20on%20its%20belly.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F655789e336d588dc55d24d96%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%222560%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EThe%20researchers%20observed%20the%20serotine%20bat%20in%20the%20attic%20of%20a%20church%20and%20a%20bat%20rehabilitation%20center.%3Cp%3EOlivier%20Glaizot%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3ESerotine%20bats%20are%20found%20all%20over%20Europe%2C%20according%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fanimaldiversity.org%2Faccounts%2FEptesicus_serotinus%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EAnimal%20Diversity%20Web%3C%2Fa%3E.%20This%20study%20focused%20on%20a%20population%20of%20bats%20living%20in%20the%20attic%20of%20a%20Dutch%20church%20and%20in%20a%20bat%20rehabilitation%20center%20in%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EPeople%20at%20the%20church%20and%20rehab%20center%20were%20observing%20the%20bats%20using%20cameras%20set%20up%20under%20a%20grid%20that%20the%20animals%20could%20climb%20on.%20Fasel%20and%20his%20team%20obtained%20the%20footage%20and%20scanned%20through%20it%20specifically%20for%20mating%20examples%2C%20and%20they%20weren't%20disappointed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20researchers%20observed%2097%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Frare-video-seal-inflates-nose-like-ballon-in-mating-ritual-2022-9%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emating%20rituals%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Each%20time%2C%20instead%20of%20putting%20its%20penis%20inside%20a%20partner's%20vagina%2C%20the%20male%20bats%20used%20it%20as%20a%20sort%20of%20arm%2C%20to%20move%20the%20female%20bat's%20tail%20membran