%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F122543%2Fnortheast-racism-another-idea%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Epeople%20from%20the%20Northeast%3C%2Fa%3E%20migrate%20outside%20the%20region%20for%20higher%20studies%20or%20employment%20because%20of%20the%20situation%20back%20home.%20Layered%20with%20my%20queerness%2C%20one%20of%20my%20dreams%20as%20a%20young%20person%20was%20to%20get%20out%20of%20this%20region%20not%20because%20I%20hated%20it%20but%20to%20explore%20myself%20further%20and%20understand%20what%20I%20was%20going%20through.%20I%20wanted%20to%20see%20the%20world%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20finishing%20high%20school%20in%20Manipur%2C%20Sadam%20studied%20at%20a%20varsity%20in%20Assam%2C%20following%20which%20he%20went%20for%20his%20master%E2%80%99s%20degree%20in%20Kerala.%20This%20was%20followed%20by%20an%20MPhil%20and%20PhD%20in%20Development%20Studies%20from%20the%20Tata%20Institute%20of%20Social%20Sciences%20(TISS)%20in%20Mumbai.%20Despite%20all%20this%20progress%2C%20Sadam%20was%20still%20dealing%20with%20a%20loss%20he%20hadn%E2%80%99t%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20yet.%C2%A0%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CAfter%20my%20father%E2%80%99s%20passing%20in%202010%2C%20I%20became%20more%20anxious%20and%20insecure%20living%20away%20from%20Manipur.%20It%20also%20started%20getting%20harder%20for%20me%20to%20come%20out%20of%20the%20closet%20because%20my%20mother%20was%20in%20mourning.%20Even%20though%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20come%20out%20to%20my%20family%20at%20one%20point%2C%20I%20kept%20it%20quiet%20(bottled%20up)%20for%20a%20very%20long%20time%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMumbai%20was%20supposed%20to%20be%20the%20answer%20but%20Sadam%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20relate%20with%20the%20fast%20pace%20of%20life%20there%2C%20and%20he%20grew%20lonelier.%20Depression%20started%20to%20take%20hold%20because%20of%20all%20the%20things%20he%20was%20hiding%20from%20his%20family.%20But%20going%20back%20home%20wasn%E2%80%99t%20an%20option%20because%20it%20was%20not%20safe%20for%20queer%20people.%20Also%2C%20going%20back%20would%20have%20meant%20giving%20up%20on%20his%20academic%20pursuits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEventually%2C%20he%20met%20someone%20on%20a%20dating%20app%20for%20queer%20people.%20Given%20his%20fragile%20mental%20state%2C%20a%20little%20hope%20was%20enough%20to%20ignite%20that%20desire%20and%20love%20for%20another%20person.%20Instead%2C%20this%20relationship%20became%20his%20gateway%20to%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F227644%2Fnagaland-hero-dimapur-can-youth-jenpu-rongmei-unemployed-youth-entrepreneur-india-nor41%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Esubstance%20abuse%3C%2Fa%3E.%20He%20began%20dabbling%20with%20crystal%20meth%20(methamphetamine)%20and%20mephedrone%20in%202015%20while%20studying%20in%20Mumbai.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CDrugs%20became%20an%20outlet%20for%20me%20to%20not%20feel%20lonely%20anymore%2C%20be%20myself%20at%20least%20for%20a%20given%20moment%20and%20escape%20my%20harsh%20realities%20and%20traumas.%20A%20lot%20of%20drug%20use%20in%20the%20gay%20community%20is%20triggered%20by%20loneliness%20and%20rejection%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMatters%20came%20to%20a%20head%20in%202017%20when%20he%20overdosed%20for%20the%20first%20time%20while%20working%20on%20his%20PhD.%20At%20the%20time%2C%20Section%20377%20of%20the%20Indian%20Penal%20Code%20(IPC)%20%E2%80%94%20which%20among%20other%20things%20criminalised%20homosexual%20acts%20%E2%80%94%20was%20also%20in%20force.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhat%20followed%20was%20a%20series%20of%20traumatic%20events.%20Instead%20of%20care%2C%20support%20and%20treatment%2C%20the%20Mumbai%20hospital%20where%20Sadam%20was%20admitted%20called%20the%20police.%20The%20hospital%20said%20that%20they%20wouldn%E2%80%99t%20treat%20Sadam%20until%20an%20FIR%20was%20registered.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CEven%20though%20I%20was%20hospitalised%2C%20the%20kind%20of%20stigma%20and%20discrimination%20I%20faced%20from%20the%20hospital%20authorities%20and%20the%20police%20was%20traumatic.%20Hospitals%20are%20supposed%20to%20be%20safe%20spaces%20where%20you%20seek%20help%2C%20care%20and%20support%20when%20you%E2%80%99re%20not%20well.%20At%20my%20most%20vulnerable%20moment%2C%20a%20policeman%20began%20interrogating%20me%20about%20where%20I%20bought%20the%20drugs%2C%20who%20I%20bought%20it%20with%2C%20how%20much%20I%20paid%20for%20it%2C%20questions%20about%20my%20personal%20life%2C%20etc.%20I%20was%20shocked%20by%20their%20lack%20of%20empathy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20the%20police%20questioned%20his%20peers%2C%20Sadam%20was%20outed%20as%20a%20gay%20man.%20Under%20the%20threat%20of%20police%20coercion%2C%20they%20had%20given%20up%20his%20queer%20identity%20without%20his%20consent.%20By%20the%20time%20his%20brother%20reached%20Mumbai%20from%20Manipur%20following%20the%20overdose%2C%20he%20also%20received%20this%20information.%20His%20family%20couldn%E2%80%99t%20believe%20that%20Sadam%20was%20gay%20since%20he%20didn%E2%80%99t%20fit%20the%20popular%20tropes%20or%20stereotypes%20associated%20with%20a%20homosexual%20identity.%20They%20struggled%20to%20come%20to%20terms%20with%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20his%20first%20overdose%2C%20Sadam%20was%20sent%20back%20home%20to%20Manipur%20for%20psychiatric%20treatment.%20The%20hospital%20even%20gave%20him%20a%20prescription%20for%20heavy%20medication%20for%20recovery.%20After%20four%20months%2C%20he%20was%20deemed%20to%20be%20better%20and%20sent%20back%20to%20Mumbai%20for%20his%20studies.%20But%20within%20a%20month%20of%20his%20return%20to%20Mumbai%2C%20he%20relapsed%20and%20overdosed%20again.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20was%20admitted%20to%20the%20same%20hospital%2C%20but%20this%20time%20they%20put%20him%20behind%20bars%20in%20an%20isolation%20ward%20and%20chained%20his%20hands%20to%20a%20hospital%20bed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CThis%20was%20such%20a%20traumatic%20episode%20that%20I%20was%20literally%20dead%20inside.%20I%20was%20dead%20out%20of%20shame%20and%20the%20nasty%20treatment%20I%20endured%20at%20the%20hands%20of%20the%20authorities.%20Instead%20of%20creating%20an%20environment%20where%20they%20would%20see%20me%20as%20a%20person%20in%20need%20of%20help%2C%20the%20hospital%20denied%20it.%20I%20was%20then%20passed%20on%20from%20one%20hospital%20and%20doctor%20to%20another%2C%20and%20given%20more%20medication.%20But%20nobody%20cared%20to%20listen%20to%20the%20reasons%20why%20I%20suffered%20from%20addiction%20and%20overdosed.%20Nobody%20was%20there%20to%20understand%20my%20pain%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFollowing%20the%20overdose%2C%20Sadam%20dropped%20out%20of%20his%20PhD%20programme%20and%20came%20back%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CIn%20my%20mind%2C%20one%20drug%20overdose%20episode%20was%20reasonable%2C%20but%20I%20had%20slipped%20up%20again.%20But%20at%20my%20lowest%20moment%2C%20I%20thought%20to%20myself%20that%20if%20I%20survived%20this%2C%20I%20really%20wanted%20to%20be%20myself.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20live%20this%20life%20of%20fakeness.%20I%20didn%E2%80%99t%20care%20if%20anybody%20thought%20I%20was%20mad.%20I%20thought%20to%20myself%20that%20if%20I%20lived%20again%20for%20the%20third%20time%2C%20I%20would%20want%20to%20be%20myself%20without%20any%20fear.%20And%20this%20process%20began%20with%20accepting%20myself%20with%20all%20the%20vulnerabilities%20that%20I%20carried%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20says.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20acceptance%20allowed%20Sadam%20to%20start%20his%20journey%20towards%20recovery.%20It%20also%20sowed%20the%20seeds%20of%20Ya_All%2C%20which%20among%20other%20things%2C%20seeks%20to%20create%20safe%20spaces%20for%20queer%20people%20in%20Manipur.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%E2%80%9CFrom%20that%20moment%20on%2C%20I%20began%20advocating%20for%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.thebetterindia.com%2F327134%2Fqueer-comedian-navin-noronha-on-navigating-comedy-circuit-in-india%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Equeer%20people%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20saying%20if%20you%20need%20help%20just%20reach%20out%20to%20me.%20I%20started%20giving%20out%20my%20phone%20number%20to%20anyone%20who%20needed%20to%20talk%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20recalls.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cdiv%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-image%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%201080px)%20100vw%2C%201080px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSnapinsta.app_343408108_911945260027500_1922232294268149346_n_1080-1700225408.jpg%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221080%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Fighting%20for%20Queer%20rights%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSnapinsta.app_343408108_911945260027500_1922232294268149346_n_1080-1700225408.jpg%201080w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSnapinsta.app_343408108_911945260027500_1922232294268149346_n_1080-1700225408-300x263.jpg%20300w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSnapinsta.app_343408108_911945260027500_1922232294268149346_n_1080-1700225408-500x438.jpg%20500w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSnapinsta.app_343408108_911945260027500_1922232294268149346_n_1080-1700225408-768x672.jpg%20768w%2C%20https%3A%2F%2Fen-media.thebetterindia.com%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F11%2FSnapinsta.app_343408108_911945260027500_1922232294268149346_n_1080-1700225408-150x131.jpg%20150w%5C%22%20class%3D%5C%22wp-image-334362%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%22945%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%20class%3D%5C%22wp-element-caption%5C%22%3ESadam%20Hanjabam%20found%20acceptance%20at%20the%20end%20of%20a%20dark%20tunnel.%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3ERecovery%20by%20creating%20a%20support%20system%C2%A0%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUpon%20his%20return%20to%20Imphal%20in%20late%202017%2C%20Sa